cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a method for video object segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves clustering visually similar segments, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MM) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions tracking and filling in missing segments, which could involve graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the paper compares its performance to recent automatic methods, which could involve machine learning (cs.MM) or computational statistics (cs.LG).
